text.section:
Questions to be voted upon shall be placed on the ballot in the following order:
those relating to the creation or adoption of a new State Constitution;
those proposing amendments to the Maryland Constitution;
those relating to other enactments of the General Assembly;
those relating to the creation or adoption of, or the amendment or other change in, the charter of a county;
those relating to other enactments by the governing body of a county; and
other questions.
